#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:178
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:180
msgid ""
"Several frameworks have been created to help implement operators by "
"generating stubs for some or all of the components. The Istio operator "
"was created with the help of a combination of `kubebuilder "
"<https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/kubebuilder>`_ and `operator "
"framework <https://github.com/operator-framework>`_. Istio’s installation"
" now uses a proto to describe the API such that runtime validation can be"
" executed against a schema."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:188
msgid ""
"More information about the implementation can be found in the README and "
"ARCHITECTURE documents in the `Istio operator repository "
"<https://github.com/istio/operator>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:193
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:195
msgid ""
"Starting in Istio 1.4, Helm installation is being replaced by new "
"``istioctl`` commands using a new operator custom resource definition, "
"``IstioControlPlane``, for the configuration API. An alpha controller is "
"also available for early experimentation with the operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:200
msgid ""
"The new ``istioctl`` commands and operator controller both validate "
"configuration schemas and perform a range of checks for installation "
"change or upgrade. These checks are tightly integrated with the tools to "
"prevent common errors and simplify troubleshooting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:205
msgid ""
"The Istio maintainers expect that this new approach will improve the user"
" experience during Istio installation and upgrade, better stabilize the "
"installation API, and help users better manage and monitor their Istio "
"installations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/introducing-istio-operator/index.rst:210
msgid ""
"We welcome your feedback about the new installation approach at "
"`discuss.istio.io <https://discuss.istio.io/>`_."
msgstr ""

